    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-hemolysis-flowrate-3lpm",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis index validation at 3 L/min nominal flow",
      "description": "CFD-predicted hemolysis index compared against in-vitro measurements at 3 L/min, 3000 RPM operating point. Predicted NIH = 0.0042 g/100 L; measured NIH = 0.0038 ± 0.0006 g/100 L. Percent error 10.5%. Uncertainty in experimental measurements discussed qualitatively in the validation report; variability attributed to pump-to-pump manufacturing tolerances and blood sample donor variability. Monte Carlo propagation of inlet velocity and viscosity uncertainties was performed at the system level and is documented in the overall UQ summary report.",
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": "https://uofa.net/synth/uq/monte-carlo-system-level"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-hemolysis-flowrate-5lpm",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis index validation at 5 L/min nominal flow",
      "description": "CFD-predicted hemolysis index compared against in-vitro measurements at 5 L/min, 3000 RPM operating point. Predicted NIH = 0.0031 g/100 L; measured NIH = 0.0028 ± 0.0005 g/100 L. Percent error 10.7%. Aleatory variability in experimental blood samples is acknowledged in prose within the validation report. The spread across repeated experiments is noted as consistent with donor-to-donor biological variability. No formal UQ artifact is linked to this specific result; uncertainty characterization is embedded in the system-level Monte Carlo summary."
    },
