      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis index validation at 6 L/min nominal flow",
      "description": "CFD-predicted hemolysis index compared against in-vitro measurements at 6 L/min, 3600 RPM operating point. Predicted NIH = 0.0025 g/100 L; measured NIH = 0.0023 ± 0.0004 g/100 L. Percent error 8.7%. Biological variability in hemolysis measurements is acknowledged; the coefficient of variation across five repeated experiments was 14%, consistent with known aleatory variability in hemolysis assays.",
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": "https://uofa.net/synth/uq/monte-carlo-system-level"
