      "rationale": "Three to four blood samples used per operating point; minimum of five not achieved at all conditions. Donor age not recorded. Statistical power analysis absent. Aleatory variability in blood properties across donors is a known source of hemolysis measurement scatter but is not formally characterized. Flagged as not-assessed."
